      "SummaryText": "automatic vents, automatic exhaust fans, an alarm system and an emergency shutoff system.\r\n\r\nIV. THE FIVE-YEAR ACCIDENT HISTORY\r\nThere have been no accidents at the MSUD WTP facility in the last five years.\r\n\r\nV. EMERGENCY RESPONSE PROGRAM\r\nThe EAP includes written safety procedures, emergency response procedures and includes the procedure for notifying the public and other affected agencies of an emergency. The WTP coordinates its EAP with the local agency of emergency management.  Annual class training, an on-site safety committee and the use of Material Safety Data Sheets keep employees aware of the hazards and safe use of chlorine. The EAP is available for review at the MSUD office.  \r\n \r\nVI. PLANNED CHANGES TO IMPROVE SAFETY\r\nThe MSUD WTP is continually training its employees and looking for new equipment or technology that will improve safety at the facility for its employees and surrounding community."
